reviewText:
The actors were great in this horribly written show. I think even more than the annoyingly bad writing, was the edited music. It had nothing to do with the scenes. They must have just chosen a score and slapped it on the final cut. The comedy was forced in the character played by Biggs. The conversations and interactions between the women show that this was a man writing what he THOUGHT women would say when they're alone. Do your research. Talk to a female friend! It was super unrealistic.

The storyline, itself, could have come together into something nice, especially with Tichina Arnold and Rockmond Dunbar. Countess Vaughn is great but she was very "Parker-ish" in this movie. Unfortunately, many urban playwrights think that if they pull in headliners, they don't have to develop their story. Worked on me! smh...
I always buy Je'caryous's plays soon as they hit the market.  This one I liked, but wasn't crazy about.  It felt as though he didn't give as much storyline as I hoped for.

I really enjoyed this film. Mrs. Arnold was great and she made an annoying character sweet. The entire cast was great. Bigg Gipps character was way too vulgar and immature. I never met anyone that stupid. Otherwise the script was well written. I think Brely Evans is gorgeous and I want to see more of her. Mr. Johnson is very talented and I enjoy most of his work. He definitely explores different topics. This film addresses issues such as faithfulness, weight, self esteem and forgiveness. Highly recommended for fans of romantic comedies with an African American cast.
I liked the fact that the not so skinny woman got the man.  I also liked that what attracted the man was substantive instead of superficial.

I like original storylines, and this is too similar to the movie "Something Borrowed". Originality is the key...sorry!! I hope you don't get in trouble for plagiarism.

Once again.. I must keep repeating myself by staying that I AM A BLACK MAN!! Just so when I make such comments it won't get twisted grin the facts... I am also from the Caribbean.. And where I am from.. We do not support messing around with two biological sisters at the same time..What kind of Nastiness is that message to be sending out to the black community.. And then to even suggest that the Man involved in this Nastiness still get his cake and eat it too... You writers still suck with your make ego huh!!!!... You still think it's a""man's world "".. Trust me you did that to my biological sister.. I would beat you in the ground... My 3 sons do that... I would beatThem in the ground too..
